## Responsibilities

1. Reconcile duplicates across extractor outputs.
2. Re-check every item's `match_existing` against the vault context;
   extractors may have missed near-matches.
3. Plan synthesis pages in `21 SYNTHESIS/` when the source
   introduces ≥ 3 connected atomics on a shared topic. Follow this
   anatomy for every proposed synthesis page:

{{ synthesis_anatomy }}
4. Filter `related_sources` to ≤ 10 entries, dropping any already
   present under `10 SOURCES/` per the vault context.
5. Preserve every extractor's `proposed_body` and
   `proposed_frontmatter` unless reconciliation requires merging.
6. Preserve each extractor item's `id` verbatim on the corresponding
   composed item. The post-composer merge step pairs items by id;
   a renamed id silently drops its judge issues.
7. When a proposed synthesis covers atomic items that carry issues,
   the merge step will only attach issues to the atomics it has
   paired verdicts for. Synthesis items stay issue-free by design.

Ultrathink about edge cases where the same concept surfaces under
different names across extractors before emitting the reconciled
items.

Return status DONE with the workdir path when every builder call
has returned ok.
